<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Twenty-seventh session 
</b></p>
<p>Agenda item 3 
</p>
<p><b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil, 
</b></p>
<p><b>political, economic, social and cultural rights, 
</b></p>
<p><b>including the right to development 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Bahrain,</b><footnote name="*">Non-member State of the Human Rights Council.  </footnote><b> China, Egypt,</b><footnote name="*">Non-member State of the Human Rights Council.  </footnote><b> Russian Federation, United Arab Emirates, Venezuela 
</b></p>
<p><b>(Bolivarian Republic of): amendment to draft resolution A/HRC/27/L.24 
</b></p>
<p><b>  27</b>/&#8230;  <b>Civil society space 
</b></p>
<p>Paragraph 4 <i>should read</i> 
</p>
<p>4. <i>Emphasizes </i>the importance of civil society space for empowering persons 
</p>
<p>belonging to national, ethnic, linguistic and religious minorities and persons in vulnerable 
</p>
<p>situations, as well as persons espousing minority beliefs, and in that regard calls upon 
</p>
<p>States to ensure that legislation, policies and practices do not undermine the enjoyment of 
</p>
<p>their human rights or the activities of civil society in defending their rights; 
</p>
